ographic material provides an extremely significant record of local Aboriginal perspectives on histories of mining and development in their regions."--cProvided by publisher.  aIssued also in electronic format.  a8 0aMineral industrieszCanada, Northern. 0aMineral industrieszCanada, NorthernxHistory. 0aOral historyzCanada, Northern. 5aNative peopleszCanada, NorthernxHistory. 6aMinesxIndustriezCanada (Nord) 6aMinesxIndustriezCanada (Nord)xHistoire. 6aAutochtoneszCanada (Nord)xHistoire. 6aHistoire oralezCanada (Nord)1 aKeeling, Arn,eauthor,eeditor.1 aSandlos, John,d1970-eauthor,eeditor.1 tMining and communities in Northern Canada.kCanadian history and environment serieskCanadian history and environment seriesw(CaOONL)20159051487 0aCanadian history and environment series ;v3.  aHD 9506 C22 M56 2015wLCc1i34917001377345lON_SHELFmKEYANOp$34.95rYsYtBOOKu2/25/2015o.STAFF. Feb24/15 MW PO 50427; no copy record01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/nb2007015388bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/119763859